SIMPLE: trapdoor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trapdoor
<hw>Trap"door`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A lifting or sliding door covering an opening in
a roof or floor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A door in a level for regulating
the ventilating current; -- called also <altname>weather
door</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Trapdoor spider</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any one
of several species of large spiders which make a nest consisting of a
vertical hole in the earth, lined with a hinged lid, like a trapdoor.
Most of the species belong to the genus <gen>Cteniza</gen>, as the
California species (<spn>Cteniza Californica</spn>).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trape</ent>⟦br⟧
